AB
C
|AB| = |AC| + |CB|
x=t, y = mt + b.
t_1, t_2
A
B
A = (t_1, mt_1 + b), B = (t_2, mt_2 + b).
t_1 < t_2.
t
t_1 < t < t_2
C
|AB|^2 = (t_2 - t_1)^2 + (mt_2 - mt_1)^2,
|AC|^2 = (t - t_1)^2 + (mt - mt_1)^2,
|CB|^2 = (t_2 - t)^2 + (mt_2 - mt)^2.
|AB|^2 = (|AC| + |CB|)^2
\angle ACB
\triangle ABC
|AB|^2 = |AC|^2 + |CB|^2 - 2 |AC| |CB| \cos \theta.
\theta \to \pi,
|AB|^2 \to |AC|^2 + |CB|^2 + 2 |AC| |CB| = (|AC| + |CB|)^2,
|AB| = |AC| + |CB|.
